      <h1 class="content-hero-title">Ayahuasca: Effects, Preparation &amp; Ceremony</h1>
      <p class="content-hero-subtitle">Ayahuasca is a psychoactive brew prepared from the Banisteriopsis caapi vine and DMT-containing plants — most commonly Psychotria viridis. It is a living ceremonial tradition, a powerful healing tool, and one of the most pharmacologically complex psychedelic substances in use. This guide covers what ayahuasca is, how it works, what the experience involves, the critical safety considerations, and the ethical dimensions of non-Indigenous engagement.</p>
